commit.message: Fix the build on old GHCs

Fix warnings with building with GHC 9.6

* After GHC 8.6, `TypeInType`'s functionality was made a part of the `DataKinds`
  and `PolyKinds` extensions. Moreover, GHC 9.6 gives a deprecation warning when
  using `TypeInType`, so we now have an extra incentive to only enable
  `TypeInType` where absolutely necessary.

* `base-4.18.*` re-exports `liftA2` from the `Prelude`, so make sure to guard
  `Control.Applicative` imports with the appropriate CPP.

Only require Functor for Eq/Ord Coyoneda instances when using transformers-0.4.*

When building with all other versions of `transformers`, the `Functor` instance
is entirely redundant.
Allow building with transformers-0.6.* and mtl-2.3.*

Adapt to (~) becoming a type operator

`(~)` now requires `TypeOperators` in GHC 9.4 (see
https://gitlab.haskell.org/ghc/ghc/-/wikis/migration/9.4?version_id=503a517b7238e8bac3dd588f32e234bf74b17097#-is-now-a-type-operator)
to build without warnings.
